race.comment: SECURITY SPOT (1) stalked the lead after a clean break from the tricky draw and went on to finish second (22.01) at this track in a Grade 6 over 381m. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Winning claims. RIPPIN' PEDRO (2) turned spotting a big start finishing seventh (22.91) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Should be about the money. TIANA BANANA (3) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at this track over 381m behind Tori Keeping (22.46) in a Grade 6. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Expected to feature in the finish. INTENSIFIED (7) cannot be ruled out.
